<item>
            <title>[LU-18940] hsm: Add BLOCKING flag for implicit restores</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18940</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I propose we add an HSM request flag to indicate that an action has been triggered by the kernel and a user process is currently blocked on this action. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;AFAICT, the &lt;tt&gt;hsm_user_request.hr_flags&lt;/tt&gt; field is currently unused by the kernel or any of the user tools or tests in the tree, so we can use this field for this flag. I also don&apos;t see any flags defined, so perhaps it could be  something like &lt;tt&gt;HR_BLOCKING&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;HR_SYNC&lt;/tt&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like &lt;tt&gt;ll_layout_restore()&lt;/tt&gt; is used when we need to trigger to restore from the kernel, so that is probably the right place to put this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
